The paper deals with the problem of finding maximum matchings of points in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT) to prove its results. The study of matchings and partitions of points can also be considered a problem in combinatorial data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on maximizing a certain objective function could also be relevant to optimization and algorithm design (cs.SI).
